prerequisite_name: cos (A+B) = cos A cos B – sin A sin B (formula 5)
dependent_name: cos 2A = cos^2 A – sin^2 A (formula 6)
explanation: cos 2A is the special case of the cosine sum formula with B = A (i.e., cos(A+A)). The text orders formula 5 before 6 and the double-angle form follows by setting B = A.

prerequisite_name: sin (A+B) = sin A cos B + cos A sin B (formula 7)
dependent_name: sin 2A = 2 sin A cos A (formula 11)
explanation: sin 2A is the special case of the sine sum formula with B = A (i.e., sin(A+A)). The text lists formula 7 before formula 11, implying this direct derivation.

prerequisite_name: cos (A–B) = cos A cos B + sin A sin B (formula 4)
dependent_name: 2 cos A cos B = cos (A+B) + cos (A–B) (formula 17)

prerequisite_name: cos (A+B) = cos A cos B – sin A sin B (formula 5)
